725048f-a.text:
Eighteenth Ave. (left) (Fourth Ave.), at the N.W. corner of 126th Street (North 17th Street), showing what was once the former College Point Hotel. In 1873 it was operated by J.M. Donnelly, although owned by Thomas 2oeller and then known as the 2oeller House. Geo. Weher owned it
in 1898.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725047f-a.text:
18th Avenue, south side, east from 126th to 127th Streets. Beers's 1873 atlas shows the first three houses to have been the property of C. Poppenhousen, and the last one of E. G.
Siefert.
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932
